 NIGERIA youngster Terem Moffi won his first man of the match award in the Belgium First Division after his heroics in  KV Kortrijk’s come back 2-2  draw against  Club Brugge on Sunday. The Bruggeers raced to a 0-2 lead thanks to Simon Deli and Federico Ricca before Ilombe Mboyo pull one back with three minutes left to halftime.  Substitute Moffi had just spent a minute on the field after replacing compatriot Imoh Ezekiel at half time before netting pass Simon Mignolet in the 47th minute to draw level for  his first goal for De Kerels. Moffi, 20, recently signed a contract for three and a half years after he fired 20 goals in the Lithuanian top league this past season. 